# ==== Git Cheat Sheet for Dopeonomics ====

# Branching Strategy

## Create new iteration branch
git checkout -b iteration/1-core-infrastructure-main

## Create each project task branch under iteration
git checkout -b /iteration/1-core-infrastructure/refactor-supply-tab

## Create bugfix or hotfix from outside the project plan
git checkout -b bugfix/fix-plan-card-expansion
git checkout -b hotfix/reset-clears-keys

# Pushing and PR

## Push new branch
git push -u origin <branch-name>

## Merge feature into iteration
git checkout iteration-1-core-infrastructure
git merge feature/iteration-1-core-infrastructure/refactor-supply-tab

## Create PR from current branch
gh pr create --base <target-branch> --fill

## Merge iteration into main (Use PR instead)
git checkout main
git merge iteration-1-core-infrastructure

# Cleanup

## Delete local & remote branches
git branch -d <branch-name>
git push origin --delete <branch-name>

# GitHub CLI (if available)

## Authenticate (once)
gh auth login

# Before PR

## Check status and test
git status
npm run lint
npm run test

# Tip:
# Keep iteration branches clean; squash minor commits into meaningful ones:
git rebase -i HEAD~<n>
